title: Athlete of the Week - Annika Lanning
text:
slideshow 
Annika Lanning - Sequoyah - Volleyball 
Annika Lanning was a spark for Sequoyah in a second-round state playoff match against Glynn Academy. The sophomore setter kept the Lady Chiefs’ offense rolling in the straight-sets win, recording 32 assists in the match. 
How long she’s played volleyball: Eight years Favorite thing about the sport: The relationships and excitement it creates Favorite color: Blue Favorite movie: She’s the Man Favorite musical artist: Luke Bryan Dream vacation: Hawaii Dream car: A dark-gray Jeep Wrangler Favorite sports team: Texas volleyball Plans for after college: Become a physical therapist
